differentiation.中释: 变异，[生物] 分化；区别

inconsequential.中释: 不重要的；不合理的；不合逻辑的

interchangeable.中释: 可互换的；可交换的；可交替的
interchangeable.英释: things that are interchangeable can be used instead of each other

desertification.英释: the process by which useful land, especially farmland, changes into desert

electrification.英释: The electrification of a house, town, or area is the connecting of that place to a supply of electricity
